{"article_id":"zezPCU1Hc2zpjKrt","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"More than 20 western allies have ordered the expulsion of dozens of Russian diplomats","depth":9},{"id":1,"text":"in response to the nerve agent attack in the UK ,","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"in a show of solidarity","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"that represents the biggest concerted blow to Russian intelligence networks in the west since the cold war .","depth":9},{"id":4,"text":"Over 100 Russian diplomats","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"alleged to be spies in western countries","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"are being told to return to Moscow , in a coordinated response to the use of a chemical weapon in the attempted murder of Sergei Skripal ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"a former Russian intelligence official , and his daughter , Yulia , in Salisbury on 4 March .","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"In a sombre statement in the House of Commons , Theresa May welcomed","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"what she said","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"was \" the largest collective expulsion of Russian intelligence officers in history \" .","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"Play Video 1:07","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"Theresa May :","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"' largest collective expulsion of Russian intelligence officers in history ' - video","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"\" I have found great solidarity from our friends and partners in the EU , North America , Nato and beyond over the past three weeks","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"as we have confronted the aftermath of the Salisbury incident , \"","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"the prime minister said .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"\" And together we have sent a message","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"that we will not tolerate Russia ' s continued attempts","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"to flout international law","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"and undermine our values. \"","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"She added :","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"\" If the Kremlin ' s goal is to divide and intimidate the western alliance ,","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"then their efforts have spectacularly backfired . \"","depth":8},{"id":24,"text":"The Russian government called the expulsions \" a provocative gesture \"","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"and said","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"it would retaliate in kind ,","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"raising the prospect of further tit-for-tat expulsions ,","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"as the US and Europe left the door open for additional measures .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"The Kremlin said","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"Vladimir Putin would make the final decision ,","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"and the Russian embassy in the US launched a poll on Twitter","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"asking which US consulate in Russia should be closed .","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"The US has ordered the expulsion of 60 Russian officials","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"who Washington says","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"are spies ,","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"including a dozen","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"based at the United Nations ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"and told Moscow to shut down its consulate in Seattle ,","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"which would end Russian diplomatic representation on the west coast .","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"The EU members Germany , France and Poland are each to expel four Russian diplomats with intelligence agency backgrounds .","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"Lithuania and the Czech Republic said","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"they would expel three ,","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"and Denmark , Italy and the Netherlands two each .","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"Estonia , Latvia , Croatia , Finland , Hungary , Sweden and Romania each expelled one Russian .","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"Iceland announced","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"it would not be sending officials to the World Cup in Russia .","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"Ukraine ,","depth":12},{"id":48,"text":"which is not an EU member ,","depth":12},{"id":49,"text":"is to expel 13 Russian diplomats ,","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"while Albania , an EU candidate member , ordered the departure of two Russians from the embassy in Tirana .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"Macedonia , another EU candidate , expelled one Russian official .","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"Canada announced","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"it was expelling four diplomatic staff","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"serving in Ottawa and Montreal","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"who","depth":13},{"id":56,"text":"the Canadian government said","depth":13},{"id":57,"text":"were spies .","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"A pending application from Moscow for three more diplomatic posts in Canada is being denied .","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"Australia confirmed","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"that it too would expel two Russian diplomats","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"who were in the country as undeclared intelligence officers ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"giving them seven days to leave .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"Raj Shah , a White House spokesperson , told reporters Monday","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"that the US expulsions were part of \" a coordinated effort \" .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"He added","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"that Donald Trump \" spoke with many foreign leaders , European allies and others","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"and encouraged them to join with the United States in this announcement \" .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"Shah described the expulsions as \" an important message","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"to send to Russia","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"and significant to degrading their intelligence capabilities \" .","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"By the close of the day a small \" coalition of the unwilling \" inside the EU had indicated to the UK Foreign Office","depth":5},{"id":72,"text":"that they were not prepared to expel any Russian diplomats in solidarity with the UK .","depth":5},{"id":73,"text":"The eight countries were Portugal , Austria , Bulgaria , Cyprus , Malta , Slovakia , Slovenia and Luxembourg .","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"Belgium and Ireland made no announcements","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"but have indicated","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"action will be taken after cabinet meetings .","depth":7},{"id":77,"text":"The UK expelled 23 Russian diplomats in the wake of the poisoning ,","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"and Russia responded","depth":7},{"id":79,"text":"by ejecting the same number of British diplomats .","depth":7},{"id":80,"text":"The Russian foreign ministry issued a statement","depth":7},{"id":81,"text":"denouncing the expulsions as \" an unfriendly step \"","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"based on alliances rather than evidence .","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"\" The provocative gesture of the so-called solidarity of these countries with London ,","depth":9},{"id":84,"text":"which blindly followed the British authorities in the so-called Skripal case","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"and which never got around to sort out the circumstances of the incident ,","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"is a continuation of the confrontational policy","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"to escalate the situation , \"","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"the statement said .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"The UK has refused to provide a sample of the nerve agent to Russia","depth":5},{"id":90,"text":"but has supplied one to the Organisation for the Prohibition of Chemical Weapons","depth":7},{"id":91,"text":"( OPCW ) ,","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"which is conducting its own investigation .","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"A senior US official said","depth":5},{"id":94,"text":"the expulsions and the Seattle consulate closure were in response to \" a reckless attempt by the [ Russian ]","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"government to murder a British citizen and his daughter with a military-grade nerve agent \" .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"A second official said","depth":5},{"id":97,"text":"the measures were also intended as a response to a \" steady drumbeat of destabilising and aggressive actions \" by Moscow against the US and its allies .","depth":5},{"id":98,"text":"Timeline","depth":3},{"id":99,"text":"Poisoned umbrellas and polonium :","depth":4},{"id":100,"text":"Russian-linked UK deaths","depth":4},{"id":101,"text":"Show Hide","depth":4},{"id":102,"text":"Georgi Markov","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"In one of the most chilling episodes of the cold war , the Bulgarian dissident was poisoned with a specially adapted umbrella on Waterloo Bridge .","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"As he waited for a bus ,","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"Markov felt a sharp prick in his leg .","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"The opposition activist ,","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"who was an irritant to the communist government of Bulgaria ,","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"died three days later .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"A deadly pellet","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"containing ricin","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"was found in his skin .","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"His unknown assassin is thought to have been from the secret services in Bulgaria .","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"Alexander Litvinenko","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"The fatal poisoning of the former FSB officer sparked an international incident .","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"Litvinenko fell ill","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"after drinking tea","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"laced with radioactive polonium .","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"He met his killers in a bar of the Millennium hotel in Mayfair .","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"The pair were Andrei Lugovoi","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"- a former KGB officer turned businessman ,","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"who is now a deputy in Russia ' s state Duma -","depth":14},{"id":122,"text":"and Dmitry Kovtun , a childhood friend of Lugovoi ' s from a Soviet military family .","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"Putin denied all involvement","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"and refused to extradite either of the killers .","depth":9},{"id":125,"text":"German Gorbuntsov","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"The exiled Russian banker survived an attempt on his life","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"as he got out of a cab in east London .","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"He was shot four times with a silenced pistol .","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"He had been involved in a bitter dispute with two former business partners .","depth":8},{"id":130,"text":"Alexander Perepilichnyy","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"The businessman collapsed","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"while running near his home in Surrey .","depth":12},{"id":133,"text":"Traces of a chemical","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"that can be found in the poisonous plant gelsemium","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"were later found in his stomach .","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"Before his death , Perepilichnyy was helping a specialist investment firm uncover a $ 230m Russian money-laundering operation ,","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"a pre-inquest hearing was told .","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"Hermitage Capital Management claimed","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"that Perepilichnyy could have been deliberately killed","depth":14},{"id":140,"text":"for helping it uncover the scam","depth":15},{"id":141,"text":"involving Russian officials .","depth":15},{"id":142,"text":"He may have eaten a popular Russian dish","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"containing the herb sorrel on the day of his death ,","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"which could have been poisoned .","depth":12},{"id":145,"text":"Boris Berezovsky","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"The exiled billionaire was found hanged in an apparent suicide","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"after he had spent more than decade waging a high-profile media battle against his one-time protege Putin .","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"A coroner recorded an open verdict","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"after hearing conflicting expert evidence about the way","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"he died .","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"A pathologist","depth":15},{"id":152,"text":"who conducted a postmortem examination on the businessman ' s body","depth":15},{"id":153,"text":"said","depth":14},{"id":154,"text":"he could not rule out murder .","depth":13},{"id":155,"text":"Scot Young","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"An associate of Berezovsky","depth":15},{"id":157,"text":"whom he helped to launder money ,","depth":15},{"id":158,"text":"he was found impaled on railings","depth":14},{"id":159,"text":"after he fell from a fourth-floor flat in central London .","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"A coroner ruled","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"that there was insufficient evidence of suicide .","depth":13},{"id":162,"text":"But Young ,","depth":14},{"id":163,"text":"who was sent to prison in January 2013","depth":15},{"id":164,"text":"for repeatedly refusing to reveal his finances during a divorce row ,","depth":15},{"id":165,"text":"told his partner","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"he was going to jump out of the window","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"moments before he was found .","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"Skripal poisoning","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"Sergei Skripal and his daughter Yulia were were found unconscious on a bench in the Maltings shopping centre in Salisbury after 'suspected exposure to an unknown substance '","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"which was later identified as chemical weapon novichok .","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"In the aftermath Theresa May blamed Vladimir Putin","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"and expelled 23 Russian diplomats","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"who were suspected of spying .","depth":12},{"id":174,"text":"Two Russian men","depth":14},{"id":175,"text":"using the identities Ruslan Boshirov and Alexander Petrov","depth":14},{"id":176,"text":"were named as suspects .","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"They appeared on Russian TV","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"to protest their innocence .","depth":13},{"id":179,"text":"The Skripals survived .","depth":12},{"id":180,"text":"However a local woman , Dawn Sturgess , died","depth":13},{"id":181,"text":"after spraying novichok on her wrists from a fake Nina Ricci perfume bottle","depth":14},{"id":182,"text":"converted into a dispenser ,","depth":15},{"id":183,"text":"which had been recovered from a skip by her partner Charlie Rowley .","depth":15},{"id":184,"text":"The alleged spies","depth":11},{"id":185,"text":"being expelled from the US","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"include 48 in the Russian embassy in Washington and 12 at the Russian mission at the UN ,","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"who","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"the US says","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"are engaged in \" aggressive collection here in the US \" .","depth":12},{"id":190,"text":"US officials said","depth":10},{"id":191,"text":"the spies at the UN were abusing their residence privileges under the UN headquarters agreement .","depth":10},{"id":192,"text":"They said","depth":10},{"id":193,"text":"there were more than 100 Russian spies in the US","depth":10},{"id":194,"text":"and the expulsions would significantly reduce Russian espionage capabilities in the country .","depth":9},{"id":195,"text":"The expelled Russians have seven days to leave the country .","depth":7},{"id":196,"text":"Mark Simakovsky , a former Russia desk director at the Pentagon , said","depth":9},{"id":197,"text":"the mass expulsions by such a large number of countries","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"acting in concert","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"were unprecedented ,","depth":10},{"id":200,"text":"but Moscow still had plenty of ways to spy on the west .","depth":8},{"id":201,"text":"\" Most Russian intelligence operations are not being done by agents","depth":10},{"id":202,"text":"acting under cover of diplomatic protocols , \"","depth":10},{"id":203,"text":"said Simakovsky , now a senior non-resident fellow at the Atlantic Council .","depth":9},{"id":204,"text":"\" Most likely , the poisoning of the Skripals was not done by anyone in an embassy or consulate . \"","depth":8},{"id":205,"text":"Daniel Fried , a former state department sanctions coordinator , said","depth":7},{"id":206,"text":"the only measures","depth":9},{"id":207,"text":"likely to have real effect on Putin ' s behaviour","depth":9},{"id":208,"text":"would be sanctions","depth":9},{"id":209,"text":"aimed at Russian money in the west .","depth":9},{"id":210,"text":"\" This is impressive","depth":9},{"id":211,"text":"but it is still the standard playbook , \"","depth":9},{"id":212,"text":"Fried said .","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"\" If we are serious about this ,","depth":9},{"id":214,"text":"we ought to think outside the box .","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"I would start going after the money ,","depth":10},{"id":216,"text":"and make clear","depth":11},{"id":217,"text":"that Russia is not going to find the west a convenient place","depth":12},{"id":218,"text":"to do business .","depth":12},{"id":219,"text":"That means going after London real estate ,","depth":10},{"id":220,"text":"and you can ' t do that","depth":11},{"id":221,"text":"without getting Miami and New York involved . \"","depth":11},{"id":222,"text":"The White House issued a statement","depth":8},{"id":223,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":224,"text":"the US was acting to \" make clear to Russia","depth":10},{"id":225,"text":"that its actions have consequences \" .","depth":10},{"id":226,"text":"Trump did not comment on Twitter , his usual form of expression on issues","depth":8},{"id":227,"text":"he feels strongly about .","depth":8},{"id":228,"text":"Expulsions of Russians are pushback against Putin 's hybrid warfare","depth":7},{"id":229,"text":"|","depth":8},{"id":230,"text":"Patrick Wintour Read more","depth":8},{"id":231,"text":"While other members of his administration have spoken out strongly against Russia , in particular for its interference in the 2016 US election ,","depth":8},{"id":232,"text":"Trump has avoided saying or tweeting anything critical of the Kremlin ,","depth":9},{"id":233,"text":"and last week defied his advisers","depth":11},{"id":234,"text":"in congratulating Putin","depth":11},{"id":235,"text":"on winning an election","depth":11},{"id":236,"text":"generally seen as closed and unfair .","depth":11},{"id":237,"text":"A senior US official said on Monday","depth":9},{"id":238,"text":"that the nature of the Russian response to UK allegations had helped convince the administration","depth":10},{"id":239,"text":"that the Kremlin was culpable .","depth":10},{"id":240,"text":"\" Russia has had nearly a month to respond","depth":11},{"id":241,"text":"but","depth":13},{"id":242,"text":"instead of explaining","depth":13},{"id":243,"text":"has engaged in the usual obfuscation","depth":13},{"id":244,"text":"we have seen in the past , \"","depth":13},{"id":245,"text":"a US official said ,","depth":10},{"id":246,"text":"noting","depth":10},{"id":247,"text":"that Moscow had put out a series of conflicting stories","depth":11},{"id":248,"text":"and attempted to put the blame on others , including the US .","depth":11},{"id":249,"text":"EU heads of state concluded last week","depth":8},{"id":250,"text":"that it was highly likely the Russian state was responsible for the attack .","depth":8},{"id":251,"text":"The EU is also looking at coordinated steps","depth":8},{"id":252,"text":"to rein back Russian hybrid warfare .","depth":8}],"relations":[{"parent":505,"left":350,"right":504,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":350,"left":329,"right":349,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":329,"left":323,"right":328,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":323,"left":276,"right":322,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":266,"right":275,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":266,"left":260,"right":265,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":260,"left":256,"right":259,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":256,"left":254,"right":255,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":254,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":255,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":259,"left":257,"right":258,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":257,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":258,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":265,"left":262,"right":264,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":262,"left":8,"right":261,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":261,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":264,"left":11,"right":263,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":263,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":275,"left":272,"right":274,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":272,"left":268,"right":271,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":268,"left":267,"right":16,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":267,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":271,"left":17,"right":270,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":270,"left":18,"right":269,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":269,"left":19,"right":20,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":274,"left":21,"right":273,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":273,"left":22,"right":23,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":322,"left":314,"right":321,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":314,"left":291,"right":313,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":291,"left":280,"right":290,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":280,"left":24,"right":279,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":279,"left":277,"right":278,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":277,"left":25,"right":26,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":278,"left":27,"right":28,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":290,"left":283,"right":289,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":283,"left":281,"right":282,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":281,"left":29,"right":30,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":282,"left":31,"right":32,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":289,"left":287,"right":288,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":287,"left":285,"right":286,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":33,"right":284,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":284,"left":34,"right":35,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":286,"left":36,"right":37,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":288,"left":38,"right":39,"relation":"causal","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":313,"left":309,"right":312,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":309,"left":302,"right":308,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":302,"left":297,"right":301,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":297,"left":40,"right":296,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":296,"left":293,"right":295,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":293,"left":292,"right":43,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":292,"left":41,"right":42,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":295,"left":44,"right":294,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":294,"left":45,"right":46,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":301,"left":299,"right":300,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":299,"left":298,"right":49,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":298,"left":47,"right":48,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":300,"left":50,"right":51,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":308,"left":307,"right":58,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":307,"left":52,"right":306,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":306,"lef